WEBVTT

00:08.239 --> 00:09.473
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "WEEDS"...</i>

00:09.507 --> 00:12.476
GENTLEMEN,
I SELL MARIJUANA.

00:12.510 --> 00:15.079
THE PROFITS
ARE ALMOST INSTANTANEOUS.

00:15.112 --> 00:17.214
WE CAN FUNNEL IT
WHEREVER WE NEED IT.

00:17.248 --> 00:19.150
I NEED MESSENGERS ‐‐
GOOD‐LOOKING MESSENGERS.

00:19.183 --> 00:21.685
YOU MAKE ONE COMMENT ABOUT WHAT
YOU'D LIKE TO DO TO SOMEONE

00:21.719 --> 00:23.053
IF YOU HAD THEM
NAKED AND TIED UP...

00:23.087 --> 00:24.522
WHEN JILL AND I
WERE SPLIT UP,

00:24.555 --> 00:27.057
I DIDN'T GET TO SEE
SHAYLA AND TAYLOR ALL THAT MUCH.

00:27.091 --> 00:28.325
[ GUNSHOT ]

00:28.359 --> 00:29.827
[ SIREN WAILING ]

00:29.860 --> 00:30.694
Silas: MOM?

00:30.728 --> 00:31.629
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

00:31.662 --> 00:33.030
AAH!

00:33.063 --> 00:36.100
IS SHE ALIVE?
YES. HOWEVER,
SHE IS IN A COMA.

00:36.133 --> 00:38.169
IF WE SEE THE SWELLING HAS COME
DOWN, WE'LL BRING HER OUT.

00:38.202 --> 00:39.703
WE'RE WORKING SHIT OUT.
YEAH.

00:39.737 --> 00:41.939
WE'RE FULL OF EMOTION.
Shane:
I'M NOT IN COLLEGE.

00:41.972 --> 00:43.207
I'M IN
THE POLICE ACADEMY.

00:43.240 --> 00:44.642
WE'RE CRIMINALS.

00:44.675 --> 00:46.076
IT'S THE FAMILY BUSINESS.
WHAT THE FUCK ARE YOU DOING?

00:46.110 --> 00:47.478
I THINK
I WANT TO BE A COP.

00:47.511 --> 00:49.914
HEY, MOM, ANY IDEA
WHO SHOT YOU IN THE HEAD?

00:49.947 --> 00:51.615
I THOUGHT
I'D FEEL BETTER.

00:51.649 --> 00:53.217
BUT I DON'T.

00:53.250 --> 00:57.721
[ BREATHING DEEPLY ]

01:05.296 --> 01:08.432
♪♪ LITTLE BOXES ON THE HILLSIDE ♪♪

01:08.466 --> 01:11.202
♪♪ LITTLE BOXES
MADE OF TICKY‐TACKY ♪♪

01:11.235 --> 01:14.205
♪♪ LITTLE BOXES, LITTLE BOXES ♪♪

01:14.238 --> 01:17.108
♪♪ LITTLE BOXES ALL THE SAME ♪♪

01:17.141 --> 01:20.344
♪♪ THERE'S A GREEN ONE
AND A PINK ONE ♪♪

01:20.377 --> 01:22.813
♪♪ A BLUE ONE AND A YELLOW ONE ♪♪

01:22.847 --> 01:25.950
♪♪ AND THEY'RE ALL MADE
OUT OF TICKY‐TACKY ♪♪

01:25.983 --> 01:29.453
♪♪ AND THEY ALL LOOK THE SAME ♪♪

01:31.422 --> 01:34.358
♪♪ AND THE PEOPLE IN THE HOUSES ♪♪

01:34.391 --> 01:36.861
♪♪ ALL GO TO UNIVERSITY ♪♪

01:36.894 --> 01:40.197
♪♪ AND THEY ALL GET
PUT IN BOXES ♪♪

01:40.231 --> 01:42.800
♪♪ LITTLE BOXES ALL THE SAME ♪♪

01:42.833 --> 01:46.103
♪♪ AND THERE'S DOCTORS
AND THERE'S LAWYERS ♪♪

01:46.137 --> 01:48.606
♪♪ AND BUSINESS EXECUTIVES ♪♪

01:48.639 --> 01:51.575
♪♪ AND THEY'RE ALL MADE
OUT OF TICKY‐TACKY ♪♪

01:51.609 --> 01:55.579
♪♪ AND THEY ALL LOOK THE SAME ♪♪

01:58.716 --> 02:00.718
[ CLICKING ]

02:09.894 --> 02:12.763
[ PRINTER WHIRRING ]

02:12.797 --> 02:16.767
Woman: "IT HAS A CAP
IN THE KITCHEN."

02:16.801 --> 02:18.803
THAT MAKES NO SENSE.

02:18.836 --> 02:20.771
A CAP IN THE KITCHEN?

02:20.805 --> 02:22.339
IT'S MOREL.

02:22.373 --> 02:25.042
M‐O‐R‐E‐L ‐‐
IT'S A MUSHROOM.

02:25.075 --> 02:27.244
I'VE SEEN THAT CLUE
BEFORE.

02:27.278 --> 02:31.482
UM, A MUSHROOM HAS A CAP...
IN THE KITCHEN.

02:31.515 --> 02:33.017
MOREL.

02:33.050 --> 02:35.920
[ GASPS ]
YES. THAT WORKS.

02:35.953 --> 02:37.588
I LIKE CROSSWORDS.

02:37.621 --> 02:43.427
BY THE WAY,
WELCOME TO ROOM 343.

02:43.461 --> 02:48.132
MY OLD NEIGHBOR
WASN'T HERE LONG ‐‐ DIED.

02:48.165 --> 02:52.136
MY OLD, OLD NEIGHBOR,
THOUGH, WENT HOME QUICK...

02:52.169 --> 02:55.806
FULL RECOVERY ‐‐
BALLOONS, LOTS OF FAMILY ‐‐

02:55.840 --> 02:59.009
YOU'RE THE POST ROAD SHOOTING,
AREN'T YOU?

02:59.043 --> 03:00.611
I...

03:00.644 --> 03:02.546
OH, YES.
POST ROAD SHOOTING.

03:02.580 --> 03:04.281
[ CHUCKLES AWKWARDLY ]
THAT'S ME.

03:04.315 --> 03:05.549
NANCY. HI.

03:05.583 --> 03:09.286
EVERYONE IN TOWN
KNOWS YOUR STORY.

03:09.320 --> 03:12.823
HOW MUCH IS ENOUGH?
THAT'S WHAT I WANT TO KNOW.

03:12.857 --> 03:15.626
WHEN THEY'VE KILLED OFF
YOUR WHOLE BLOODLINE...

03:15.659 --> 03:17.928
THEY ‐‐
...AFTER WHAT THEY DID
TO YOUR FATHER

03:17.962 --> 03:20.331
OUT IN THE NEVADA DESERT,

03:20.364 --> 03:22.733
AND YOUR GRANDFATHER.

03:22.767 --> 03:25.269
THE INCINERATOR IN SICILY.
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

03:25.302 --> 03:26.570
Shane: HEY, MOM.

03:27.671 --> 03:28.572
SHANE.

03:28.606 --> 03:31.542
I'LL GO DO
THE PONY EXPRESS?

03:31.575 --> 03:34.879
WAIT. UM...

03:34.912 --> 03:36.747
I'LL GO WITH YOU.
HELP ME.

03:43.354 --> 03:46.957
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

03:46.991 --> 03:49.760
LET'S DO IT!

03:49.794 --> 03:52.730
[ WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER P. A. SYSTEM ]

03:52.763 --> 03:53.964
SO, WE'RE MAFIA?

03:53.998 --> 03:56.333
YEAH, THE COPS READ
"MEXICAN MAFIA" IN YOUR FILE,

03:56.367 --> 03:58.736
AND IT GOT RE‐INTERPRETED
AS "MAFIA MAFIA"

03:58.769 --> 04:00.838
ON THE OLD SANDWICH
GOSSIP CIRCUIT.

04:00.871 --> 04:03.674
AUNT JILL WORKS IT IN TOWN,
PARKS IN THE HANDICAPPED SPOTS.

04:03.707 --> 04:05.276
JILL CORLEONE.

04:05.309 --> 04:07.745
SHE DOES THE JERSEY ACCENT.
IT'S KIND OF SAD.

04:07.778 --> 04:10.214
I HAVE SOMETHING
I WANT TO SHOW YOU.

04:10.247 --> 04:12.883
IS THAT FROM SCHOOL?
YEAH.

04:12.917 --> 04:15.486
HONEY, I‐I KNOW
I'VE BEEN PRETTY OUT OF IT,

04:15.519 --> 04:18.422
BUT I'VE BEEN SO IMPRESSED
WITH YOUR...

04:20.991 --> 04:22.293
Y‐‐ [ SIGHS ]

04:22.326 --> 04:24.895
LIKE A TRAIN,
HOW IT KEEPS GOING UP A HILL.

04:24.929 --> 04:26.964
CHUG‐CHUG. "I THINK I CAN,
I THINK I CAN..."

04:26.997 --> 04:28.132
PERSEVERANCE.
FORTITUDE.

04:28.165 --> 04:29.934
YES! BOTH.

04:29.967 --> 04:31.402
[ SIGHS ]

04:31.435 --> 04:32.403
CRAP.

04:32.436 --> 04:34.805
AT LEAST I GOT "MOREL."

04:36.307 --> 04:38.876
MAIL CALL!

04:38.909 --> 04:41.278
Woman: OH, YOU GOT ME
THE SUDOKU BOOK! I LOVE YOU!

04:41.312 --> 04:44.348
[ CHUCKLES ]
HAVE A GOOD ONE.

04:44.381 --> 04:48.018
SO, RED LINES ARE PEOPLE
WHO WANT YOU DEAD FOR REVENGE.

04:48.052 --> 04:51.021
YELLOW LINES ARE PEOPLE WHO
WOULD PROFIT FROM YOUR DEMISE,

04:51.055 --> 04:52.423
BUT FOR THEM,
IT'S LESS PERSONAL.

04:52.456 --> 04:53.958
AS YOU CAN SEE,
WE'RE MOSTLY RED ‐‐

04:53.991 --> 04:56.560
GUILLERMO, CESAR,
HEYLIA.

04:56.594 --> 04:58.762
EDUCATED MONEY SAYS
IT'S GUILLERMO OR ‐‐

04:58.796 --> 05:01.065
BE NICE.
BE NICE?

05:01.098 --> 05:03.801
SON‐ASSISTED THERAPY ‐‐
I LIKE IT.

05:03.834 --> 05:07.004
AND HOW ARE WE DOING
ON THE STAIR TEST, YOUNG LADY?

05:07.037 --> 05:08.839
ON MY WAY THERE
RIGHT NOW.

05:08.873 --> 05:11.041
YOU GET UP THOSE STAIRS, I'LL
HAVE YOU BACK IN YOUR OWN BED

05:11.075 --> 05:12.443
BY TOMORROW NIGHT...

05:12.476 --> 05:14.945
OR WHOEVER ELSE'S BED
YOU WANT TO END UP IN.

05:14.979 --> 05:17.348
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

05:18.349 --> 05:20.885
I'M GONNA MISS YOUR MOTHER
VERY MUCH

05:20.918 --> 05:22.319
WHEN SHE LEAVES HERE,
SHANE.

05:22.353 --> 05:26.223
SHE'S BEEN A...BEAM OF SUNSHINE
FOR ALL OF US.

05:26.257 --> 05:27.324
Woman on P. A. system:
<i>DR. DOLEGNOW, 3211.</i>

05:27.358 --> 05:29.493
YOU'RE VERY LUCKY
TO HAVE HER.

05:29.527 --> 05:31.695
<i>DR. DOLEGNOW, 3211.</i>

05:31.729 --> 05:32.830
BEAM OF SUNSHINE?

05:32.863 --> 05:35.266
THAT'S ME.

05:35.299 --> 05:38.502
IT'S AMAZING WHAT
A .22‐CALIBER SLUG WILL DO.

05:39.470 --> 05:41.939
BURN THAT DIAGRAM.
PROMISE ME.

05:41.972 --> 05:44.408
MOM, I ‐‐
I'M SERIOUS.

05:44.442 --> 05:46.444
YOU AVOID THIS TOPIC
EVERY TIME I BRING IT UP.

05:46.477 --> 05:49.580
IF YOU DO COME HOME TOMORROW,
WHOEVER DID THIS...

05:55.519 --> 05:57.822
...MIGHT COME BACK
AND TRY TO FINISH THE JOB.

05:57.855 --> 05:58.956
HE WON'T.

05:58.989 --> 06:00.624
HOW CAN YOU BE
SO SURE?

06:00.658 --> 06:03.093
SHANE,
I KNOW BECAUSE I KNOW.

06:03.127 --> 06:06.230
HE GOT WHAT HE CAME FOR,
AND HE REGRETS IT.

06:06.263 --> 06:08.065
YOU KNOW WHO DID IT.

06:08.099 --> 06:10.201
HOW COULD I KNOW,
SWEETIE?

06:10.234 --> 06:12.837
[ Breathlessly ]
OH, GOD.

06:12.870 --> 06:14.672
OKAY.

06:14.705 --> 06:16.740
I NEED TO...SIT DOWN

06:16.774 --> 06:19.710
AND...STOP TALKING.

06:21.011 --> 06:22.480
YOU'LL TRY AGAIN LATER.

06:22.513 --> 06:24.815
RIGHT.

06:27.284 --> 06:29.153
SPIDER.

06:29.186 --> 06:31.322
COME ON.

06:32.623 --> 06:34.758
SPIDER DOING PUSH‐UPS
ON A MIRROR.

06:34.792 --> 06:36.694
[ LAUGHS ]

06:37.995 --> 06:40.097
DING‐DONG!
DING‐DONG!

06:40.131 --> 06:41.432
DING‐DONG, DING‐DONG,
DING‐DONG!

06:41.465 --> 06:44.235
Andy:
OKAY! OKAY, TAYLOR.

06:44.268 --> 06:45.669
I GOT IT. I GOT IT.

06:45.703 --> 06:48.139
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]
WHAT'S GOING ON?

06:48.172 --> 06:49.840
YOU HAVE COMPANY.

06:49.874 --> 06:52.576
GUESS I'M GONNA HAVE TO
TAKE A RAIN CHECK
ON THAT LAST PART.

06:52.610 --> 06:54.345
NOT AN ISSUE.

06:54.378 --> 06:56.814
AWW, INSULATION.
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:56.847 --> 06:57.948
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

06:57.982 --> 06:59.650
NO.
I WAS HOPING.

06:59.683 --> 07:01.252
DADDY'S HERE.

07:02.553 --> 07:05.322
HEY, HEY, HEY. IT'S
"UNCLE SCOTT," STEVIE.
WE TALKED ABOUT THIS.

07:05.356 --> 07:09.393
WHAT A NICE SURPRISE,
SCOTT.

07:09.426 --> 07:11.362
ANDY,
GOOD TO SEE YOU,

07:11.395 --> 07:14.899
AND [CHUCKLES] APPARENTLY,
IT'S GOOD TO SEE <i>ME.</i>

07:14.932 --> 07:16.734
EXCUSE ME.
Jill: HEY, HOW, UH ‐‐
HOW WAS INDIA?

07:16.767 --> 07:18.469
Scott: GOOD. GOOD.

07:18.502 --> 07:20.037
UH, THREE WEEKS
WITH DYSENTERY

07:20.070 --> 07:21.539
GIVES YOU PLENTY OF TIME
TO THINK.

07:21.572 --> 07:24.408
YOU KNOW,
WHEN THE, UH, SKY IS GRAY,

07:24.442 --> 07:27.711
IT'S JUST CLOUDS,
NOT ACTUAL SKY.

07:27.745 --> 07:30.614
THEN THE CLOUDS PASS,
AND YOU SEE

07:30.648 --> 07:33.117
THAT THE SKY'S STILL THERE
AND IT'S STILL BLUE.

07:33.150 --> 07:36.353
THE CLOUDS
AREN'T HURTING THE SKY.

07:36.387 --> 07:37.888
THEY WERE TEMPORARY.

07:37.922 --> 07:39.824
WOW.

07:39.857 --> 07:41.158
OKAY.

07:41.192 --> 07:46.363
HEY, I, UH,
GOT SOMETHING FOR MY GIRLS.

07:46.397 --> 07:48.399
COOKIE‐DOUGH FLAVOR.

07:48.432 --> 07:50.167
I THOUGHT
THOSE WERE DISCONTINUED!

07:50.201 --> 07:52.403
I STOPPED
AT THREE WHOLE FOODS

07:52.436 --> 07:55.539
ON THE WAY HERE
FROM THE AIRPORT.

07:55.573 --> 07:57.408
MMM!

07:57.441 --> 08:01.445
BABE,
YOU GOT TO TRY IT.

08:03.214 --> 08:04.615
OH, YUM.

08:04.648 --> 08:06.450
FINISH IT.
NO, IT'S YOURS.

08:06.484 --> 08:08.185
NO.
OKAY, OKAY.

08:08.219 --> 08:11.422
SO, ANYHOW,
I AM SUPER JET‐LAGGED

08:11.455 --> 08:13.257
AND NOT TOO USED
TO WEARING SHOES.

08:13.290 --> 08:14.625
SO I'M GONNA HEAD TO MY HOTEL,

08:14.658 --> 08:16.527
BUT I WOULD BE SO GRATEFUL,
JILL,

08:16.560 --> 08:18.462
IF YOU COULD HAVE DINNER
WITH ME.

08:18.496 --> 08:21.499
THERE'S A LOT
WE NEED TO TALK ABOUT.

08:21.532 --> 08:24.902
I'LL SEE YOU GUYS LATER.

08:26.704 --> 08:30.341
DADDY, I WANT TO STAY
AT THE HOTEL WITH YOU.

08:30.374 --> 08:33.144
OH, KITTEN,
I'M NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

08:33.177 --> 08:36.380
THERE'S PLENTY OF TIME
FOR US TO TALK ABOUT
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN.

08:36.413 --> 08:38.015
EVERYTHING WILL BE FINE.

08:38.048 --> 08:40.951
COME ON.
WALK ME OUT.

08:44.989 --> 08:47.258
SHIT!
WHAT "SHIT"?

08:47.291 --> 08:48.726
HE SEES THE BLUE SKY
BEHIND THE CLOUDS.

08:48.759 --> 08:50.227
YOU SHOULD HAVE DINNER
WITH HIM.

08:50.261 --> 08:52.663
NO. HE WANTS THINGS.

08:52.696 --> 08:54.498
[ LAUGHS ]
HE WANTS TO SEE HIS KIDS.

08:54.532 --> 08:56.066
HE'S UNCOMFORTABLE
IN SHOES.

08:56.100 --> 08:58.002
HEAR HIM OUT,
DON'T AGREE TO ANYTHING,

08:58.035 --> 08:59.470
EAT,
AND THEN COME HOME.

08:59.503 --> 09:02.406
OH, I DO NEED TO FIND OUT
WHICH WHOLE FOODS HE WENT TO.

09:02.440 --> 09:03.908
I FUCKING LOVE
THESE BARS.

09:03.941 --> 09:05.443
OH.

09:07.378 --> 09:08.946
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

09:08.979 --> 09:10.414
PONY EXPRESS.

09:10.448 --> 09:13.083
LOOK AT YOU ‐‐ UP OUT OF BED,
MAKING THE ROUNDS.

09:13.117 --> 09:15.219
STAIRCASE TEST.

09:15.252 --> 09:17.087
[ GIGGLES ]
YOU'LL DO IT.

09:17.121 --> 09:19.089
WELL...

09:19.123 --> 09:21.392
PISTACHIOS.

09:22.259 --> 09:23.461
AND...

09:23.494 --> 09:25.095
DON'T KNOW
HOW YOU DRINK IT...

09:25.129 --> 09:27.231
BUT PEACH SCHNAPPS.
OH!

09:27.264 --> 09:28.532
[ GIGGLES ]

09:29.300 --> 09:31.702
HMM?
NO.

09:33.504 --> 09:35.106
MMM.

09:35.139 --> 09:36.941
I'D OFFER YOU SOME,
SHANE,

09:36.974 --> 09:39.076
BUT PEACH SCHNAPPS
IS FOR GIRLS.

09:39.110 --> 09:41.045
THANKS FOR SPARING
MY MASCULINITY.

09:41.078 --> 09:42.680
AHH.

09:42.713 --> 09:44.982
[ BREATHING DEEPLY ]

09:47.985 --> 09:49.687
THAT BAD, HUH?

09:51.188 --> 09:54.158
OH, IT'S TUESDAY,
ISN'T IT?

09:54.191 --> 09:55.960
GETTING ANYTHING
FROM THE CLOWN?

09:55.993 --> 09:58.395
THE INFAMOUS CLOWN
IS HERE?

09:58.429 --> 10:01.365
I KNOW. HE'S A RIP‐OFF,
BUT I CAN'T DO MORPHINE.

10:01.398 --> 10:03.434
IT MAKES ME
SICK TO MY STOMACH,

10:03.467 --> 10:06.370
AND...
THESE MAKE ME GIGGLE.

10:07.905 --> 10:09.940
PONY EXPRESS,
CAN YOU DO IT?

10:09.974 --> 10:10.941
IT'S ON US.

10:10.975 --> 10:12.209
THANK YOU.

10:12.243 --> 10:14.378
[ SIGHS ] ALL RIGHT.
QUICK, QUICK.

10:14.411 --> 10:17.248
IT'S THE LAST ROOM
AT THE END OF THE HALLWAY.

10:17.281 --> 10:20.818
GOT TO GET THERE FAST
BEFORE HE SELLS OUT.

10:27.387 --> 10:29.256
NO CHECKS.
CASH ONLY.

10:29.289 --> 10:30.757
Man:
THIS AIN'T FAIR.

10:30.791 --> 10:33.427
ANYONE WITH TUMORS
SHOULD GET FIRST DIBS.

10:33.460 --> 10:35.329
FUCK YOU.
I'M STAGE 4 BREAST.

10:35.362 --> 10:38.465
END‐STAGE LEUKEMIA AND
ALREADY RECOMMENDED FOR HOSPICE,

10:38.499 --> 10:39.633
SO SUCK MY DICK, PAL.

10:39.666 --> 10:41.068
WAIT YOUR TURN.

10:41.101 --> 10:45.272
UH, THREE PLEASE.
UH, LEMON, LIME, AND CHERRY.

10:45.305 --> 10:47.741
[ LAUGHS ]

10:47.775 --> 10:50.444
THOSE ARE TWENTIES.
THAT'S A HUGE MARKUP.

10:50.477 --> 10:52.946
THEY SHOULD CALL HIM
"GOUGE‐Y THE CLOWN."

10:52.980 --> 10:54.047
DOUCHE.

10:54.081 --> 10:57.151
Glenn:
COME ON, MAN, I'M IN PAIN HERE.

10:57.184 --> 10:59.953
THERE'S A REASON
THEY CALL IT "MEDICINAL."

11:05.092 --> 11:06.727
YOU OKAY?

11:09.930 --> 11:11.265
THAT GUY.

11:11.298 --> 11:13.434
YEP.

11:13.467 --> 11:16.537
WAS I LIKE THAT?
A DOUCHE?

11:16.570 --> 11:20.474
A‐A GOUGE‐Y
CLOWN DOUCHE?

11:20.507 --> 11:23.243
WELL, AT LEAST YOUR CUSTOMERS
WEREN'T SICK.

11:23.277 --> 11:26.847
SICKNESS IS RELATIVE.

11:30.017 --> 11:33.086
I THINK
I WAS A BAD PERSON.

11:35.589 --> 11:37.291
I DON'T WANT TO BE LIKE THAT
ANYMORE.

11:37.324 --> 11:39.460
OKAY. GOOD FOR YOU.

11:39.493 --> 11:41.228
N‐NO.

11:41.261 --> 11:44.298
NO.
GOOD FOR ALL OF US.

11:44.331 --> 11:46.366
WE'RE NOT GONNA BE LIKE THAT
ANYMORE.

11:46.400 --> 11:47.935
THAT WAS
THE "BEFORE" BOTWINS.

11:47.968 --> 11:51.505
NOW...
WE'RE THE "AFTER" BOTWINS,

11:51.538 --> 11:54.608
LIKE THOSE PEOPLE
ON THE WEIGHT‐LOSS ADS.

11:54.641 --> 11:57.277
"BEFORE" ‐‐ UNHAPPY.

11:57.311 --> 11:59.446
"NOW" ‐‐

11:59.480 --> 12:03.383
LOVELY
AND BETTER DRESSED...

12:03.417 --> 12:04.885
WITH OUR HAIR DONE

12:04.918 --> 12:10.424
'CAUSE WE'RE ‐‐ WE'RE FEELING
GOOD ABOUT OURSELVES, RIGHT?

12:10.457 --> 12:13.694
YOU NOTICE
HOW THEY'RE ONLY EVER SMILING

12:13.727 --> 12:15.829
IN THE "AFTER" PHOTOS?

12:15.863 --> 12:20.334
THE SMILING
MAKES A BIG DIFFERENCE.

12:21.869 --> 12:25.706
LET ME SEE YOU SMILE,
HONEY.

12:27.040 --> 12:28.909
COME ON.

12:29.977 --> 12:31.078
REALLY?

12:31.111 --> 12:33.113
MOM, THIS IS DUMB.

12:35.115 --> 12:36.650
[ SIGHS ]

12:36.683 --> 12:39.953
GO ON BACK IN THERE.
DON'T LOSE YOUR PLACE IN LINE.

12:39.987 --> 12:42.089
GET THE LOLLIPOPS
SO GRETA WILL GIGGLE.

12:42.122 --> 12:47.428
I'M TIRED.
I'M GONNA GO...BACK IN BED.

12:47.461 --> 12:49.029
YEAH, KEEP THEM COMING.

12:49.062 --> 12:52.132
WE GOT THIS BORING‐ASS
SHAREHOLDER THING WE
GOT TO DO TOMORROW.

12:52.166 --> 12:54.268
UH, KIKU SAID WE NEED TO GET
YOUR CREDIT CARD.

12:54.301 --> 12:56.937
FOR WHAT?
SHE'S CHARGING US?

12:57.971 --> 13:00.307
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]
WE'RE THE INVESTORS.

13:00.340 --> 13:02.276
WINDOW.

13:02.309 --> 13:03.377
WE MADE THAT BITCH.

13:03.410 --> 13:04.745
SORRY. KIKU SAID.

13:04.778 --> 13:06.880
WHAT BULLSHIT!
COMPANY CARD.

13:08.215 --> 13:12.152
DID YOU GET A CHANCE
TO TAKE A LOOK AT OUR PROPOSAL?

13:12.186 --> 13:13.220
REMIND ME AGAIN.

13:22.563 --> 13:25.532
OKAY, SO, EACH TRIKINI
COMES WITH ITS OWN SCARF.

13:25.566 --> 13:28.001
THAT CAN BE TIED
SIX DIFFERENT WAYS.

13:28.035 --> 13:29.603
SARONG.
SASH.

13:29.636 --> 13:31.538
HEADBAND.

13:31.572 --> 13:33.507
KERCHIEF.

13:33.540 --> 13:34.775
CAPELET.

13:35.709 --> 13:38.112
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.
SHOW ME THAT ONE AGAIN.

13:38.145 --> 13:41.648
CAPELET.
MINI‐CAPE.

13:41.682 --> 13:43.117
HOW MUCH DO YOU NEED?

13:46.153 --> 13:47.387
YOU'RE MOVING.

13:47.421 --> 13:50.257
[ MUFFLED TALKING ]

13:51.425 --> 13:53.494
IS THAT A SAFE WORD
I HEARD?

13:53.527 --> 13:55.262
[ MUFFLED TALKING ]

13:55.295 --> 13:56.563
NO.

13:56.597 --> 13:58.398
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

13:58.432 --> 14:00.100
JUST ONE THING,
AND I'LL STOP.

14:00.134 --> 14:01.635
TWO. FIRST ‐‐

14:01.668 --> 14:03.504
I PREFER YOUR HAIR DARK.
WHY CAN'T YOU DYE IT AGAIN?

14:03.537 --> 14:06.073
SECOND...YOU NEED TO TALK
TO YOUR UNCLES.

14:06.106 --> 14:08.008
THEY COME TO THE LOFT
AND TAKE FROM THE SUPPLY.

14:08.041 --> 14:10.577
AND WHIT ‐‐
IS HE EVEN RELATED TO YOU?

14:10.611 --> 14:11.945
[ MUFFLED TALKING ]

14:11.979 --> 14:15.682
AM I HERE
TO TALK ABOUT BUSINESS?

14:15.716 --> 14:17.117
[ MUFFLED GRUNT ]

14:17.151 --> 14:20.621
NO. I AM NOT HERE
TO TALK ABOUT BUSINESS.

14:20.654 --> 14:23.223
[ MUFFLED TALKING ]

14:23.257 --> 14:26.093
WHEN IS YOUR MOTHER COMING BACK?
I NEED HER HELP.

14:26.126 --> 14:28.262
I'M ABOUT TO RUN OUT OF SUPPLY,
AND I CAN'T ‐‐

14:28.295 --> 14:31.064
[ GASPS ]
AHH...

14:31.098 --> 14:33.133
YOU DONE?

14:33.167 --> 14:35.002
I'M NOT SURE.

14:35.035 --> 14:37.271
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

14:37.304 --> 14:38.639
YOU THINK
YOU CAN STAY QUIET?

14:38.672 --> 14:40.073
PROBABLY NOT.

14:40.107 --> 14:41.775
[ GASPS ]

14:45.012 --> 14:46.180
[ MUFFLED GRUNT ]

14:46.213 --> 14:47.748
HELLO?

14:49.049 --> 14:50.384
SURE.

14:50.417 --> 14:53.353
WHEN DO YOU NEED IT?

14:53.387 --> 14:57.257
I CAN BE THERE IN...

14:57.291 --> 14:58.492
TWO HOURS.

14:58.525 --> 14:59.960
[ CHUCKLES ]

14:59.993 --> 15:02.996
BYE, MOM.

15:03.964 --> 15:07.034
[ SIGHS ]
OBSTACLE COURSE AGAIN.

15:07.067 --> 15:10.003
HE SAID 85%, RIGHT?

15:10.037 --> 15:11.772
SORRY?
IN CLASS.

15:11.805 --> 15:14.808
SERGEANT SALZBERG SAID 85%
OF ALL MALE JUVENILE OFFENDERS

15:14.842 --> 15:16.543
COME
FROM FATHERLESS HOMES.

15:16.577 --> 15:19.980
[ SCOFFS ]
NOT TOO SURPRISING, RIGHT?

15:20.013 --> 15:23.917
YOUR FATHER DIES.
YOU GO OFF THE RAILS.

15:23.951 --> 15:26.753
YOU PUNISH EVERYBODY
ANY WAY YOU CAN.

15:26.787 --> 15:28.622
[ SCOFFS ]
YOU'VE GIVEN THIS SOME THOUGHT.

15:28.655 --> 15:32.659
DEAD FATHER, PSYCH MAJOR,
EXPERT ON THE TOPIC.

15:32.693 --> 15:34.495
BUT YOU'RE NOT
OFF THE RAILS.

15:34.528 --> 15:35.896
YOU'RE HERE,
AND I'M HERE,

15:35.929 --> 15:38.398
AND WE'RE BOTH
IN THE "DEAD DADDY" CLUB.

15:38.432 --> 15:41.335
WELL, LOOK AT THAT ‐‐
KINDRED SPIRITS.

15:41.368 --> 15:42.936
MAYBE WE'RE JUST

15:42.970 --> 15:46.373
TWO SLEEPER CELLS OF RAGE
WAITING TO EXPLODE,

15:46.406 --> 15:48.008
AND THIS IS OUR WAY
TO GET THE GUNS.

15:48.041 --> 15:49.143
YOU'RE DARK.

15:49.176 --> 15:50.878
YOU TALKING SHIT
ABOUT MY SKIN TONE NOW?

15:50.911 --> 15:55.282
UH...NO. I‐I DIDN'T ‐‐
I JUST ‐‐ JUST...

15:56.383 --> 15:57.718
FUCKING WITH YOU.

15:57.751 --> 16:01.155
COME ON. LET'S DO
THIS STUPID OBSTACLE COURSE.

16:04.858 --> 16:08.262
WE SHOULD HAVE MADE SUGAR.
EVERYONE LIKES SUGAR COOKIES.

16:08.295 --> 16:12.332
I WAS THINKING
15, 18 BUCKS EACH...

16:12.366 --> 16:13.734
MAYBE 20?

16:13.767 --> 16:16.236
I STEEPED THE BUTTER
FOR A LONG TIME

16:16.270 --> 16:17.938
IN MY STRONGEST STRAIN.

16:17.971 --> 16:19.873
NO ONE'S GONNA NEED
MORE THAN A BITE TO FEEL IT.

16:19.907 --> 16:21.875
WE'RE NOT TAKING ANY MONEY
FOR THEM.

16:21.909 --> 16:23.610
HUH?

16:23.644 --> 16:27.548
IT'S NOT RIGHT
TO PROFIT FROM PAIN, HONEY.

16:27.581 --> 16:29.082
WE'RE NOT
THAT KIND OF PEOPLE.

16:30.851 --> 16:35.989
MY MOTHER WORKED
IN ‐‐ IN GIFT WRAP

16:36.023 --> 16:37.157
[GASPS]

16:37.191 --> 16:40.394
AT THE HUDSON'S ON WOODWARD,
DOWNTOWN DETROIT.

16:40.427 --> 16:44.264
ALL OUR PRESENTS HAD TO BE
WRAPPED THE HUDSON'S WAY ‐‐

16:44.298 --> 16:46.533
PERFECT.

16:46.567 --> 16:50.370
CHRISTMAS MORNING
KILLED HER

16:50.404 --> 16:53.307
TO SEE US
TEAR THEM ALL APART.

16:53.340 --> 16:57.077
SHE ACTUALLY CRIED.

16:57.111 --> 16:58.245
PERFECT.

16:58.278 --> 17:01.782
WE'RE AT LEAST GONNA NEED
TO COVER OUR COSTS.

17:01.815 --> 17:05.552
HONEY, YOU'RE THINKING
LIKE "BEFORE" SILAS.

17:05.586 --> 17:07.554
DON'T BE "BEFORE" SILAS.

17:07.588 --> 17:11.458
THAT WAS THE PAST.
THAT WAS THE PROLOGUE.

17:11.492 --> 17:12.759
Come here.

17:15.295 --> 17:17.731
SMILE.

17:22.536 --> 17:23.971
[ SMOOCHES ]

17:25.139 --> 17:26.940
HERE, HELP ME WRAP.

17:26.974 --> 17:29.576
I'LL TEACH YOU
THE HUDSON'S CURL.

17:29.610 --> 17:31.411
WAS SHE NICE?

17:31.445 --> 17:33.881
MY MOTHER? NO.

18:09.983 --> 18:14.021
WHOA!
HEY, YOU CLEAN UP NICE.

18:14.054 --> 18:16.957
ARE THOSE NANCY'S SHOES
AND...DRESS?

18:16.990 --> 18:18.692
MM‐HMM.
SHE'S GONNA BE HOME SOON.

18:18.725 --> 18:20.427
I GOT TO WEAR IT
WHILE I STILL CAN.

18:20.461 --> 18:22.162
IT LOOK OKAY?
MORE THAN OKAY.

18:22.196 --> 18:23.797
WHY SO,
YOU KNOW, FANCY?

18:23.831 --> 18:26.333
IT'S CALLED
SHOVING IT IN HIS FACE.

18:26.366 --> 18:30.070
I DIDN'T WITHER ON THE VINE.
I'M THRIVING.
GOOD LOGIC.

18:30.104 --> 18:32.539
SMART. MIGHT GAIN YOU
SOME LEVERAGE WITH THE CUSTODY.

18:32.573 --> 18:34.508
CROSS YOUR LEGS A LOT
DURING DINNER SLOWLY,

18:34.541 --> 18:36.176
AND DANGLE THE SHOE
OFF YOUR FOOT.

18:36.210 --> 18:37.377
NO, THAT MIGHT BE TOO MUCH.

18:37.411 --> 18:38.812
IS HE TAKING YOU
SOMEWHERE GOOD?

18:38.846 --> 18:40.681
CHINESE. I'M GONNA HAVE
EVERYTHING ON THE MENU.

18:40.714 --> 18:42.883
I WILL ORDER EXTRA AND BRING
SOME HOME. WHAT DO YOU WANT?

18:42.916 --> 18:44.685
SESAME NOODLES.
OH, YES.

18:44.718 --> 18:48.055
GOOD CALL ON THE NOODLES.
THOSE WILL BE GREAT TOMORROW.

18:51.592 --> 18:53.961
I WON'T BE LATE.
OKAY.

18:53.994 --> 18:57.498
REMEMBER ‐‐ AGREE TO NOTHING,
JUST HEAR THE MAN OUT,

18:57.531 --> 19:00.834
BE KIND AND RESPECTFUL,
AND THINK OF THE KIDS.

19:00.868 --> 19:03.771
AND CROSS YOUR LEGS A LOT.
GOOD LUCK.

19:03.804 --> 19:08.008
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]
[ SIGHS ]

19:11.845 --> 19:14.648
[ LAUGHTER IN DISTANCE ]

19:21.321 --> 19:23.757
[ LAUGHTER CONTINUES ]

19:45.734 --> 19:47.736
[ LIGHT THUDDING ]

19:55.792 --> 19:57.661
YOU'RE OUT
OF YOUR LEAGUE.

19:57.694 --> 20:01.064
WAY THE FUCK OUT
OF YOUR LEAGUE.

20:01.097 --> 20:03.033
BACK OFF!

20:06.269 --> 20:07.938
[ DOOR OPENS ]

20:09.873 --> 20:13.176
WHEN WILL
THEY BE SATISFIED?

20:13.210 --> 20:14.844
ANIMALS.

20:14.878 --> 20:18.181
Shayla: I ALWAYS THOUGHT
WE'D STICK AROUND LONG ENOUGH
TO SEE THE "FOIL‐AGE."

20:18.215 --> 20:19.649
IT'S NOT "FOIL‐AGE."
IT'S "FOLIAGE."

20:19.683 --> 20:20.784
WHAT ARE YOU GIRLS DOING?

20:20.817 --> 20:22.519
PACKING UP.
GOING HOME.

20:22.552 --> 20:24.521
HOME? WHY?

20:24.554 --> 20:26.156
BECAUSE
THEY'RE GETTING BACK TOGETHER.

20:26.189 --> 20:28.658
THIS IS WHAT HAPPENS ‐‐
HE GETS CONTROL‐FREAKY,

20:28.692 --> 20:30.493
AND SHE GETS PISSED OFF
AND LEAVES.

20:30.527 --> 20:31.761
WE LIVE SOMEWHERE ELSE
FOR A WHILE.

20:31.795 --> 20:33.396
IT WAS SAUSALITO
LAST TIME.

20:33.430 --> 20:35.899
SHE FINDS...
A DISTRACTION.

20:35.932 --> 20:37.634
RICK.
RICK WITH THE HOUSEBOAT.

20:37.667 --> 20:39.102
DAD GIVES HER
SOME TIME.

20:39.135 --> 20:41.504
A COUPLE MONTHS.
THEN THEY HAVE DINNER.

20:41.538 --> 20:42.706
HE APOLOGIZES.

20:42.739 --> 20:43.840
SHE REMEMBERS
WHAT SHE LIKES ABOUT HIM.

20:43.874 --> 20:46.142
HE'S STABLE.
HE'S A GOOD BREADWINNER.

20:46.176 --> 20:48.778
HE TALKS ABOUT ALL THE WORK
HE'S GOING TO DO ON THE HOUSE.

20:48.812 --> 20:50.914
SHE GOT HER PAINTING STUDIO
OUT OF IT LAST TIME.

20:50.947 --> 20:52.916
SHE SITS US DOWN AND TELLS US
WE'RE GOING HOME.

20:52.949 --> 20:55.051
DID SHE SAY THAT?
SHE SAID YOU WERE GOING HOME?

20:55.085 --> 20:57.254
NOT YET.
SHE WILL.
WE'RE GETTING A JUMP START.

20:57.287 --> 21:01.258
OKAY [CHUCKLES] THIS
IS NOT GONNA HAPPEN AT ALL.

21:01.291 --> 21:02.893
THAT'S JUST...
I...

21:02.926 --> 21:05.662
JUST NEED TO MAKE
A CALL.

21:05.695 --> 21:07.330
I'LL CALL.

21:10.700 --> 21:13.236
<i>Hi, it's Jill.</i>
<i>Leave a message.</i>

21:13.270 --> 21:15.705
IT'S PROBABLY IN HER BAG. SHE
CAN'T HEAR IT IF IT'S IN HER BAG

21:15.739 --> 21:19.876
'CAUSE IT'S ZIPPED UP,
IT'S MUFFLED UNDER THE...

21:21.144 --> 21:23.113
[ MAN LAUGHING ]

21:23.146 --> 21:24.481
[ WOMAN GIGGLING ]

21:24.514 --> 21:27.651
OOH.
OH.

21:27.684 --> 21:29.519
[ BOTH GIGGLING ]

21:29.553 --> 21:31.254
YEAH.
[ GIGGLES ]

21:31.288 --> 21:32.422
[ GASPS ]

21:33.790 --> 21:36.192
Nancy:
SO SORRY TO INTERRUPT.

21:36.226 --> 21:38.061
LOOKS SUPER‐EROTIC.

21:38.094 --> 21:43.166
SMELLS LIKE...ONIONS,
THOUGH.

21:43.200 --> 21:44.534
UH...

21:44.568 --> 21:46.403
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

21:46.436 --> 21:49.606
I DON'T THINK WE'VE MET.

21:49.639 --> 21:50.874
POST ROAD SHOOTING.

21:50.907 --> 21:53.109
MAYBE
YOU'VE HEARD OF ME?

21:53.143 --> 21:54.177
MY FAMILY?

21:54.211 --> 21:55.178
COSA NOSTRA.

21:55.212 --> 21:57.180
I...HEARD THINGS.

21:57.214 --> 22:02.385
MAYBE YOU SHOULD ENLIGHTEN
DRUG‐PUSHER BOZO HERE

22:02.419 --> 22:03.920
ABOUT
WHO HE'S THREATENING.

22:03.954 --> 22:06.456
I NEED TO GET BACK
TO WORK.

22:12.662 --> 22:14.197
[ SIGHS ]

22:14.231 --> 22:18.635
NOW THAT WE'RE ALONE...
I'LL SPEAK FRANKLY.

22:18.668 --> 22:21.638
I COME
FROM A LONG LINE OF PEOPLE

22:21.671 --> 22:25.642
WHO CAN MAKE OTHER PEOPLE
DISAPPEAR, AS IF BY MAGIC.

22:25.675 --> 22:27.644
I DIDN'T KNOW.
NO, YOU DIDN'T.

22:27.677 --> 22:29.145
AND HERE I AM,

22:29.179 --> 22:32.048
TRYING TO LIVE A BETTER LIFE
AND DO THE RIGHT THING,

22:32.082 --> 22:35.585
AND YOU BRING
ALL THIS NEGATIVE SHIT INTO IT.

22:35.619 --> 22:38.054
I DON'T WANT
ANY NEGATIVE SHIT.

22:38.088 --> 22:41.925
I'VE HAD WAY TOO MUCH OF IT
ALREADY.

22:41.958 --> 22:43.760
HERE'S
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN.

22:43.793 --> 22:47.731
FROM NOW ON, PEOPLE IN PAIN ‐‐
THEY DON'T PAY.

22:47.764 --> 22:48.932
HOSPITAL WORKERS,
NURSES ‐‐

22:48.965 --> 22:51.034
I DON'T CARE.
GOUGE THEM.

22:51.067 --> 22:54.771
BUT THE PATIENTS ‐‐
THEY'RE YOUR CHARITY.

22:54.804 --> 22:58.508
PRICE OF BUSINESS.

22:58.542 --> 23:00.510
I'M...
LEAVING HERE TOMORROW,

23:00.544 --> 23:03.079
BUT I'LL BE BACK IN A WEEK
TO CHECK ON YOU.

23:03.113 --> 23:05.148
SO DON'T FUCK AROUND TO SEE
WHAT YOU CAN GET AWAY WITH.

23:05.181 --> 23:07.083
OKAY?
YEAH, OKAY.

23:11.354 --> 23:14.724
YOU'VE GOT A SECOND CHANCE
TO BE A BETTER PERSON.

23:14.758 --> 23:16.960
USE IT, OKAY?

23:23.733 --> 23:26.436
[ SIGHS ]

23:26.469 --> 23:28.338
[ BOTTLES CLINK ]

23:28.371 --> 23:29.739
I JUST ‐‐
I JUST WANT ANOTHER.

23:29.773 --> 23:30.974
YEAH, YEAH.

23:31.007 --> 23:32.442
HELLO?

23:32.475 --> 23:35.378
UM, UNO MáS? ICHI?
POR FAVOR?

23:38.148 --> 23:41.051
I'M ‐‐ I'M
JUST GONNA READ IT.

23:41.084 --> 23:43.720
"JILL, I COME TO YOU TODAY
A CLEAN SLATE ‐‐

23:43.753 --> 23:45.622
"TABULA RASA."
MMM.

23:45.655 --> 23:49.726
"EMPTY, BUT FOR ONE DESIRE ‐‐
TO START FRESH.

23:49.759 --> 23:52.696
"I HOLD NO ILL WILL
FOR THE CHOICES YOU MADE,

23:52.729 --> 23:54.598
NO GRUDGES, NO ANGER."

23:54.631 --> 23:56.633
MMM. SO GOOD.
"WE WALKED OUR PATHS ‐‐

23:56.666 --> 23:59.102
SOMETIMES DIFFICULT
AND HAZARDOUS..."
MM‐HMM.

23:59.135 --> 24:01.872
"...AND THOSE PATHS
LED US HERE."

24:01.905 --> 24:04.975
MMM.
OH, THANK YOU SO MUCH.

24:05.008 --> 24:06.743
THANK YOU.

24:16.786 --> 24:18.788
AHH.
OKAY, GO AHEAD.

24:18.822 --> 24:20.657
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

24:20.690 --> 24:23.760
"I WANT YOU TO KNOW
I REGRET WHO I ONCE WAS

24:23.793 --> 24:26.696
"AND WHAT I ALLOWED
OUR LIVES TO BECOME.

24:26.730 --> 24:28.532
I WAS A," UH...
FUCK HEAD.

24:28.565 --> 24:30.667
[ CHUCKLES ]

24:30.700 --> 24:33.169
A FUCK HEAD, YES.
[ CHUCKLES ]

24:33.203 --> 24:35.472
"I'M HERE TODAY TO ASK YOU
TO RELEASE

24:35.505 --> 24:37.173
"YOUR ASSUMPTIONS
FROM THE PAST

24:37.207 --> 24:40.143
"AND CHOOSE, INSTEAD,
TO BE LIKE THE CELLS

24:40.176 --> 24:42.946
"OF ALL CONTINUALLY REGENERATING
LIVING BEINGS

24:42.979 --> 24:47.117
WHO CANNOT BUT EXIST
INSIDE CHANGE."

24:48.485 --> 24:51.121
"UNFOLDING, UNFOLDING.

24:51.154 --> 24:54.691
"JILL, I'M NOT HERE
TO RECLAIM OUR OLD LIVES

24:54.724 --> 24:56.726
"BUT TO REDEFINE THEM,

24:56.760 --> 25:00.497
"TO TOSS OUT THE CALCIFIED
REMAINS OF THE PAST

25:00.530 --> 25:02.666
"AND EMBRACE
OUR VITAL ENERGY ‐‐

25:02.699 --> 25:05.969
"YOURS, MINE ‐‐

25:06.002 --> 25:10.106
FOR OUR SAKES, FOR OUR
BEAUTIFUL FAMILY'S SAKE."

25:10.140 --> 25:11.575
[ SIGHS ]

25:11.608 --> 25:14.211
[ SIGHS ]

25:14.244 --> 25:16.880
YOU HAVE MY VOW
THAT I WILL NO LONGER ATTEMPT

25:16.913 --> 25:19.516
TO CONTROL, LESSEN,
OR DIMINISH

25:19.549 --> 25:21.451
WHO YOU ARE
OR WHAT YOU'LL BE

25:21.484 --> 25:24.154
BUT TO EMBRACE IT,
ENTIRE.

25:26.690 --> 25:29.993
THIS WORD
IS MY TROTH.

25:30.026 --> 25:30.860
YOUR WHAT?

25:30.894 --> 25:34.965
TROTH.
T‐R‐O‐T‐H.

25:40.770 --> 25:42.839
[ BOTH PANTING ]

25:42.873 --> 25:44.341
WHY DID YOU COME HERE?

25:44.374 --> 25:46.376
I'M NOT A DISTRACTION.

25:46.409 --> 25:49.512
I'M NOT
RICK WITH THE HOUSEBOAT.

25:49.546 --> 25:51.081
YOU'RE JEALOUS?

25:51.114 --> 25:53.183
NO. YEAH.

25:53.216 --> 25:54.618
YOU CAN'T GO.

25:54.651 --> 25:56.086
THE GIRLS CAN'T GO.

25:56.119 --> 25:57.120
[ MOANING ]

25:57.153 --> 25:59.589
NOBODY CAN GO.

25:59.623 --> 26:01.491
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

26:01.524 --> 26:03.660
THIS ISN'T JUST FUCKING.

26:03.693 --> 26:05.061
THIS IS SOMETHING ELSE.

26:05.095 --> 26:06.930
[ MOANING ]
Woman: SOUNDS LIKE FUCKING
TO ME.

26:06.963 --> 26:08.598
[ DOOR CLOSES ]
THIS IS THE LADIES' ROOM.

26:08.632 --> 26:10.200
[ GASPS ]

26:10.233 --> 26:11.434
[ SIGHS ]

26:12.669 --> 26:15.906
I NO LONGER
CHOOSE TO EMBRACE

26:15.939 --> 26:18.909
ALL THAT YOU ARE, JILL,
OR WILL BE.

26:18.942 --> 26:22.379
YOU NO LONGER HAVE
MY FUCKING TROTH!

26:22.412 --> 26:25.115
PEOPLE DON'T CHANGE.
IT'S BULLSHIT!

26:25.148 --> 26:26.249
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

26:26.283 --> 26:30.153
SIX MONTHS IN INDIA
DOWN THE FUCKING GANGES!

26:30.186 --> 26:32.222
[ MOANING ]

26:34.257 --> 26:36.393
[ NANCY PANTING ]

26:53.210 --> 26:56.746
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

26:57.781 --> 26:59.349
BYE‐BYE, NANCY.

26:59.382 --> 27:02.319
OH. OH, GOODBYE.
GOOD LUCK.

27:03.486 --> 27:07.224
HEY. THANK YOU.

27:07.257 --> 27:08.391
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

27:08.425 --> 27:10.594
OH, STOP.
STOP, STOP.

27:10.627 --> 27:12.829
SWEETIE, SAY THANK YOU
TO THE CLOWN.

27:12.862 --> 27:14.931
HE'S THE ONE WHO MADE YOU
ALL THE BALLOON ANIMALS.

27:14.965 --> 27:16.867
THANK YOU, MR. CLOWN.

27:16.900 --> 27:18.468
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

27:18.501 --> 27:20.170
GOOD BOY.

27:20.203 --> 27:21.738
OKAY. SEE YOU LATER.

27:24.708 --> 27:27.110
Man:
BYE. GOOD LUCK.

27:28.278 --> 27:31.281
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

27:43.827 --> 27:46.796
